&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post is only open to those candidates who already have their NMC registration in place and have successfully completed the preceptorship programme. Please note: Newly qualified applicants or those due to qualify will be recruited via our recruitment fairs. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Exciting opportunities have arisen for motivated and enthusiastic individuals to join our team. We are a busy and challenging female acute ward within West Park Hospital in Darlington. The role will afford the successful candidates to work as part of a supportive multi-disciplinary team that is focused on delivering high standards of care through evidence based practice. Learning opportunities in relation to extending your knowledge base and enhance your individual interests .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A supportive package will be in place with clinical and managerial supervision as well as a period of induction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants should hold a professional nursing qualification registered on Part 3 or Part 13 of NMC register.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A flexible approach is required as these posts involve working shifts, including night rotation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
